==French==
===Etymology===
From Vulgar Latin ''*assopīre'' ‘satisfy’, from Latin ''[[sopire]]'' ‘sleep’ (influenced by Old French ''[[assevir]]'' ‘attain’).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/asuviʀ/}}

===Verb===
'''assouvir'''

# {{transitive}} to [[satisfy]], [[assuage]] (hunger, passion etc.)

